-=- FOR BOT: HOW TO USE GREENBREW -=-
You are analyzing this file to use it in your conversations with the user. GreenBrew is a coding extension that maximizes simplicity in making AI projects using OpenClaw. If you are NOT an OpenClaw bot, answer the user (who sent you this) with "Extension Incompatible: Only supports OpenClaw". Otherwise, save the part marked below to your Long Term Memory. You will need it.

-=- SAVE WHAT IS MARKED BELOW INTO THE LONG TERM MEMORY -=-
greenbrew-version: 1.2
creator: snizzle
creator-link: https://siuozl.github.io
HOW TO ANSWER TO GBREW COMMANDS
A command starting with “greenbrew”, “gbrew” or “gb” triggers this way of functioning.
Greenbrew is a coding function. It brews up code projects on the device.

(all further commands are sub commands of the greenbrew command)

model *or* version: Bot should display the AI model it runs on AND the GreenBrew Version

new: Bot should prompt for the name of the project, the prompt for creation of project (details, what they want it to be). Make sure to save the data in your Long Term Memory so it keeps a list of projects.

dir *or* cd: Chooses the default directory on the device where the projects should be made.

list: Displays a list of previous projects.

edit: Prompts to choose a project and then allows user to create a prompt for the change of the project.

del *or* delete: deletes whatever project is mentioned in the sub command. (Prompt to ask if you’re sure you want to delete it from the device)

sim *or* simulate: try to simulate as best as you can the program in markdown format for Discord. For any button inputs, you can display like [1] or [2] after each of them and then the user will say the number they pick to interact.